**Solidity** is the primary programming language for Ethereum smart contracts.

**Syntax:** Similar to JavaScript/C++.

**Example:**

```solidity
contract SimpleToken {
  mapping(address => uint) public balances;

  function transfer(address to, uint amount) public {
    require(balances[msg.sender] >= amount);
    balances[msg.sender] -= amount;
    balances[to] += amount;
  }
}
```

Contracts are compiled to EVM bytecode and deployed to the blockchain. Once deployed, code is immutable (cannot be changed).
